---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTA from '../components/CTA.astro';
import { business } from '../data/business';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Healthy Paws Animal Hospital"
  description="Privacy policy for Healthy Paws Animal Hospital. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your personal information."
>
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="bg-hpah-green-light py-16">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-hpah-text-light max-w-2xl">
        Your privacy matters to us. This policy explains how {business.name} collects,
        uses, and protects your personal information.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-hpah-text-light mt-4">Last updated: May 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Policy Content -->
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose">

        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          We collect information that you voluntarily provide to us when you interact with our
          practice, use our website, or communicate with our team. This may include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Personal identification information:</strong> Your name, email address, phone number, and mailing address.</li>
          <li><strong>Pet information:</strong> Your pet's name, species, breed, age, weight, and medical history.</li>
          <li><strong>Payment information:</strong> Credit card numbers and billing details processed securely through our payment processor. We do not store full credit card numbers on our systems.</li>
          <li><strong>Communication records:</strong> Emails, phone call notes, and appointment records related to your pet's care.</li>
          <li><strong>Website usage data:</strong> Information automatically collected when you visit our website, including IP address, browser type, pages visited, and time spent on each page.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Providing veterinary care:</strong> To maintain your pet's medical records, schedule appointments, and deliver veterinary services.</li>
          <li><strong>Communication:</strong> To contact you regarding appointments, follow-up care, test results, vaccination reminders, and other matters related to your pet's health.</li>
          <li><strong>Payment processing:</strong> To process payments for services rendered.</li>
          <li><strong>Practice operations:</strong> To manage our practice, improve our services, and ensure the quality of care we provide.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal compliance:</strong> To comply with applicable laws, regulations, and legal processes, including state veterinary licensing requirements and controlled substance record-keeping.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Cookies and Website Tracking</h2>
        <p>
          Our website may use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your browsing
          experience and analyze website traffic. Cookies are small data files stored on your
          device that help us understand how visitors use our website.
        </p>
        <p>We may use the following types of cookies:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Essential cookies:</strong> Necessary for the website to function properly.</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics cookies:</strong> Help us understand how visitors interact with our website so we can improve it.</li>
          <li><strong>Functional cookies:</strong> Remember your preferences and settings to enhance your experience.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You can control cookies through your browser settings. Disabling cookies may affect
          some website functionality, but will not impact your ability to contact us or receive
          veterinary care.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-Party Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties.
          We may share your information in the following limited circumstances:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Veterinary referrals:</strong> If your pet requires specialized care, we may share relevant medical records with referral veterinary specialists or emergency facilities with your consent.</li>
          <li><strong>Laboratories and diagnostic services:</strong> To process diagnostic tests and receive results for your pet's care.</li>
          <li><strong>Payment processors:</strong> To securely process credit card and other electronic payments.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal requirements:</strong> When required by law, court order, or governmental regulation, including state rabies reporting requirements.</li>
          <li><strong>Service providers:</strong> We may use third-party services for website hosting, email communication, and appointment reminders. These providers are contractually obligated to protect your information.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We take the security of your personal information seriously. We implement reasonable
          administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect your data against
          unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. These measures include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Encrypted electronic medical records systems</li>
          <li>Secure payment processing through PCI-compliant providers</li>
          <li>Restricted access to personal information on a need-to-know basis</li>
          <li>Regular security assessments of our systems and procedures</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          While we strive to protect your information, no method of transmission over the
          internet or electronic storage is completely secure. We cannot guarantee absolute
          security but are committed to maintaining the highest practical standards.
        </p>

        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Our website is not directed to children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly
          collect personal information from children under 13. If a parent or guardian becomes
          aware that their child has provided us with personal information without their consent,
          please contact us at <a href={`mailto:${business.email}`}>{business.email}</a>
          and we will promptly delete such information from our records.
        </p>

        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Request access to the personal information we hold about you</li>
          <li>Request correction of inaccurate personal information</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your personal information, subject to legal record-keeping requirements</li>
          <li>Opt out of non-essential communications (appointment reminders for active patients are considered essential)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Please note that veterinary medical records are subject to state retention requirements
          and may need to be maintained for a minimum period regardless of deletion requests.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices,
          technology, or legal requirements. When we make changes, we will update the "Last updated"
          date at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.
        </p>
        <p>
          For significant changes that affect how we handle your personal information, we will
          make reasonable efforts to notify you, such as posting a notice on our website or
          contacting you directly.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this privacy policy, your personal information,
          or our privacy practices, please contact us:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href={`tel:${business.phoneRaw}`}>{business.phone}</a></li>
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href={`mailto:${business.email}`}>{business.email}</a></li>
          <li><strong>Mail:</strong> {business.name}, {business.address.full}</li>
        </ul>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTA />
</BaseLayout>
